{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01F5Yw8MhNs7hfMmCGEkKgjx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n1. Delete the existing StatefulSet and Services\n2. Generate TLS certificates\n3. Create the required secrets (es-http-tls, elastic-password)\n4. Update the ConfigMap with ES 8.11.1 config (with TLS)\n5. Deploy the new StatefulSet\n\nLet me do this step by step. First I need to tear down the existing deployment, then create everything new.\n\nFor ES 8.11.1, I need to handle:\n- `cluster.initial_master_nodes` - required for new clusters\n- TLS for both HTTP and transport\n- Security enabled (default in 8.x)\n- The `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var to bootstrap the elastic user password\n\nI'll generate TLS certificates using openssl, creating a CA and server certificate with Subject Alternative Names covering all the Elasticsearch service endpoints (the HTTP service, headless service, individual pod DNS names, and localhost).\n\nFor transport TLS, I'll use a shared certificate across nodes for simplicity. Now I'm writing a script that will handle the full setup: cleaning up any existing resources, generating the certificates, creating the necessary secrets and configmap, and deploying the StatefulSet.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":470,"cache_read_input_tokens":32931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":470},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04b80efa-7cc4-4368-9677-082eed58964b","uuid":"321937c8-cec2-46ea-89d7-c8eb3353cdaf","request_id":"req_011CcLudsuUpiXgkWTzH8P5U"}
