{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01E9GdsehABRVXGKsueDfiFs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is running but stuck because it's trying to resolve the other ES nodes (es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2) and they don't exist yet. The StatefulSet is only spawning pods one at a time (it waits for each to become Ready before starting the next).\n\nThe issue is the readiness probe is checking for cluster health (green/yellow), but with only 1 node and `cluster.initial_master_nodes` set to 3 nodes, the cluster won't form until all 3 are up. But the StatefulSet won't start pod 1 and 2 until pod 0 is Ready.\nThis creates a deadlock: the first pod can't pass its health check until the cluster forms, but the cluster can't form until all three pods are running. I need to simplify the readiness probe to just verify that Elasticsearch is responding on HTTPS, rather than waiting for cluster health to reach green or yellow. Once all three nodes are up, they'll form the cluster naturally. Updating the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` to start all nodes simultaneously, and simplifying the readiness probe to just verify ES is responding rather than checking cluster health status.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1057,"cache_read_input_tokens":40901,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1057},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04b80efa-7cc4-4368-9677-082eed58964b","uuid":"2568daa1-b1fa-4f53-bf7c-ae46a59354c1","request_id":"req_011CcLvWfM6gE9cqNbWrHK5q"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01E9GdsehABRVXGKsueDfiFs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pod is stuck because StatefulSet waits for pod 0 to be Ready before starting pods 1 and 2, but the cluster can't be healthy with only 1/3 nodes. I need `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start simultaneously."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1057,"cache_read_input_tokens":40901,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1057},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04b80efa-7cc4-4368-9677-082eed58964b","uuid":"80be726f-db93-4312-9aa2-4eed21bfa25b","request_id":"req_011CcLvWfM6gE9cqNbWrHK5q"}
