{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0161ZPd4VWtjCiubgZvF6Xgi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The deployment is complete and fully functional. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem with previous state:** An ES 7.17.9 cluster was already deployed using the wrong image version, with no TLS or authentication, and the required secrets didn't exist.\n\n**What was deployed:**\n\n1. **TLS certificates** — Generated a CA and server cert with SANs covering all service/pod DNS names, stored in secret `es-http-tls`.\n\n2. **Password secret** — Created `elastic-password` with the bootstrap password for the `elastic` user.\n\n3. **ConfigMap `es-config`** — ES 8.11.1 config with xpack security + TLS enabled for both HTTP and transport layers.\n\n4. **Services** — Headless `es-cluster` (port 9300, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` to break the DNS bootstrap deadlock) and ClusterIP `es-http` (port 9200).\n\n5. **StatefulSet** — 3 replicas with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` (so all 3 pods start simultaneously and can form the cluster), image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`.\n\n**Result:**\n- All 3 nodes: `1/1 Ready`\n- Cluster health: **green**, 3/3 nodes\n- HTTPS reads and writes through `es-http:9200`: **working**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":54471,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":409},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04b80efa-7cc4-4368-9677-082eed58964b","uuid":"666c50f1-e9ea-4958-bc31-8c59164bc192","request_id":"req_011CcLw7ESsZ3dCqefFcuFNL"}
